 
A string is called lucky, if it contain atleast one vovel.
You are given a string and you have to find out whether it is a lucky string or not.
 

Input

The first line of the input contains an integer T denoting the number of test cases. The description of T test cases follows.
Each test case contains a single given string.

 

Output
 

Print "yes" if the given string is lucky else print "no" without quotes.

 

Constraints
Should contain all the constraints on the input data that you may have. Format it like:

1 ≤ T ≤ 10
1 ≤|string length|≤100

 

Example
Input:
2hellotwyndyllyngs

Output:
yesno
